news.title: Cuttack court orders sale of Sarala Realcon's assets for fraud
news.para: The economic offences wing (EOW) of the state Crime Branch had registered a case against Sarala Realcon Pvt Ltd, its managing director Gayadhar Jena and other directors in March 2015 for allegedly collecting about Rs 17 crore from 238 people.

news.title: Gurugram civic body's estimate to complete deficient infrastructure in four colonies ready
news.para: Officials said the highest estimate is for Vipul World, where a total amount of Rs 8.22 crore is required to complete deficient infrastructural work such as laying of road, water and sewer networks.

news.title: Shriram Housing Finance in merger talks, valuation holds the key
news.para: “There is only one active prospect that we are pursuing, but there again, valuation is a hurdle. I won’t pay recklessly to grow,” he told ET in an exclusive interaction," said managing director Ravi Subramanian.

news.title: Navi Mumbai plot sold for record Rs 5.54 lakh per sq meter
news.para: This was nearly five times the reserve base price set by Cidco at Rs 1.14 lakh a sq m. It works out to Rs 306 crore for the roughly 1.3-acre plot (5,526 sq m) located at Sector 20, Palm Beach Road, Sanpada.

news.title: Noida: 75 developers with over Rs 9,000 crore land dues start getting notices
news.para: Officials said that over the next 3-4 days, notices would be issued to about 75 developers, who owe the Authority over Rs 9,000 crore in total.

news.title: Ramgarh limestone mine in Jaisalmer goes under hammer for 21% premium
news.para: The Ramgarh block fetched a premium of 21% over the offered price. Dalmiya Bhara Green Vision won the block in the auction.

news.title: Land acquisition completed on entire line except Godrej & Boyce plot: Maharashtra to HC
news.para: Of the total 508.17 km of rail track between Mumbai and Ahmedabad, about 21 km is to be underground. One of the entry points to the underground tunnel falls on the land at Vikhroli (owned by Godrej).

news.title: Bills to regularize illegal constructions in Kerala soon
news.para: As per the amendment proposed to the Kerala Panchayat Raj Act, 1994, and the Kerala Municipality Act, 1994, all the constructions that have been initiated or have been completed prior to November 7, 2019, can be regularized.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Nine condominiums around, but this 2km stretch has no lights for over a year
news.para: Residents have been complaining about the issue for a year, but the authorities are yet to resolve it completely.

news.title: SC issues notice to Chintels India, asks how structure built recently collapsed
news.para: Advocate Prashant Bhushan, appearing for the resident petitioners of Chintels Paradiso society in Sector 109 of Gurugram, submitted that the audit of the structures reveals that the building in unsafe.

news.title: Goa: GCZMA orders demolition of hotel, shack violating CRZ rules
news.para: Three different persons had filed complaints against the illegal constructions, including former Benaulim MLA Churchill Alemao and the Colva Civic and Consumer Forum.

news.title: Maharashtra revenue department website resolves 5,000 land-related issues
news.para: The website now has over 2500 officers on board and dozens of land related queries from across the state are answered every week.

news.title: Installation of solar street light in Jamshedpur begins
news.para: With the joint contribution of the local MLA and the Jharkhand Renewable Energy Development Agency (JREDA), installation of 1,500 LED solar lights under the second phase of the project began on Saturday.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Jagananna houses to top in energy-saving
news.para: The Union government’s Energy Efficiency Services Limited (EESL) is contemplating to enter into a tripartite agreement with the Andhra Pradesh housing and energy departments to supply these energy efficient appliances at cost effective prices for the beneficiaries of this housing scheme.

news.title: Chandigarh administration council to meet on Nov 22 to discuss key issues
news.para: As some crucial issues are being under discussion with the ministry of home affairs (MHA), it will be interesting and crucial to see the views of the senior officers of the Chandigarh administration.
